      out.write("<div id=\"faqMain\"\r\n    style=\"margin:0 auto 0 auto;border:1px solid #eaeaea;width:980px;position:relative;background:#ffffff;\" class=\"clearfix\">\r\n\r\n\r\n<div id=\"faqlist\">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a href=\"#what\">What can I do with Ragic?</a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"#required\">What's required to use Ragic?</a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"#learn\">How do I learn to build Ragic applications?</a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"#share\">Can I share applications with others?</a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"#limit\">Can I limit who sees/uses my applications?</a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"#import\">Can I create a database from my spreadsheet?</a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"#export\">Can I export a database to spreadsheet?</a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"#support\">How do I get help if I need it?</a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"#safe\">Is it safe to store my data on Ragic?</a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"#kept\">How long will my data be kept?</a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"#install\">Can I install Ragic on my own computer or servers?</a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"#many\">Are there any limits to how many or how big my applications are?</a></li>\r\n");
      out.write("<li><a href=\"#publish\">Is there any place where developers can publish their own apps?</a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"#mean\">What does Ragic mean?</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div id=\"faq\">\r\n<a name=\"what\"></a>\r\n<h1>What can I do with Ragic?</h1>\r\n<p>You can use Ragic to build most of the database applications that you can think of.</p>\r\n<p>Most online form builders which is limited to individual forms that are attached to database tables. This is the reason that they don't work well when your requirement gets a little complicated.</p>\r\n<p>Ragic is free of any database tables. No matter how complicated the application is, you build it exactly the way you would as in spreadsheets.</p>\r\n\r\n<a name=\"required\"></a>\r\n<h1>What's required to use Ragic?</h1>\r\n<p>All you need is a browser and Internet connection. Your browser may be Firefox, Internet Explorer, Safari, Opera, or even browser on your mobile device.</p>\r\n\r\n<a name=\"learn\"></a>\r\n<h1>How do I learn to build Ragic applications?</h1>\r\n<p>We have a complete tutorial and documentation at our <a href=\"learn\">Ragic doc</a>.</p>\r\n");
      out.write("<p>However, we believe that the best way to learn by doing. You can think of a simple application that you and your friends would like to use and just start building. You can always check out our <a href=\"learn\">learning center</a> for some information. Or ask a question on our <a href=\"/forum/main\">forum</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Once you get started, you'll be surprised how easy it is!</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<a name=\"share\"></a>\r\n<h1>Can I share applications with others?</h1>\r\n<p>You certainly can! That's the point of a Ragic application!</p>\r\n<p>We're always surprised at how many people ask us this. When you finish your application, just put the URL on your website or blog, send it to your friends, or share on Facebook or Twitter.</p>\r\n<p>For enterprise applications, you can simply tell everyone the URL for your account home, and they will be able to access all the applications on Ragic. You can even add links to your other applications on your desktop to make Ragic your enterprise portal!</p>\r\n\r\n<a name=\"limit\"></a>\r\n<h1>Can I limit who sees/uses my applications?</h1>\r\n");
      out.write("<p>As an application designed for enterprise use. Ragic has complete access control functions. You can create user groups and assign roles to each user groups. Each roles have differently designed access privileges. You can check out our doc for more information on <a href=\"/hp/doc/html/content/ch06s06.html\">access right control</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<a name=\"import\"></a>\r\n<h1>Can I create a database from my spreadsheet?</h1>\r\n<p>Of course you can! That's a good way to get started on building Ragic applications when you already have some data on your spreadsheet files. First go to your account home, choose import your data, and follow the instructions uploading your spreadsheet file. Ragic will create an application based on your file in no time.</p>\r\n\r\n<a name=\"export\"></a>\r\n<h1>Can I export a database to spreadsheet?</h1>\r\n<p>Yes, on your Ragic Builder screen, choose [Reports] => [Download as Excel File].</p>\r\n\r\n<a name=\"support\"></a>\r\n<h1>How do I get support if I need it?</h1>\r\n<p>You can contact us anytime via our <a href=\"/support/rs\">support ticket system</a>. (Hey! It's made with Ragic of course!)</p>\r\n");
      out.write("\r\n<a name=\"safe\"></a>\r\n<h1>Is it safe and secure to store my data on Ragic?</h1>\r\n<p>We do everything technically possible to keep your data safe.</p>\r\n<p>Ragic supports AES-128 bit SSL encryption, which is the current standard for data transmission, to keep all communication safe. Ragic servers are physically protected by biometric authentication, video surveillance. We also have redundant power, UPS, cooling and fiber to keep our services reliable. We do a detailed background check on all Ragic employees as a condition of employment.</p>\r\n<p>Putting data on your computer is not always safe!</p>\r\n<p>Most people think putting enterprise data on cloud servers is unsafe, but in most conditions, the truth is just the opposite. Without good security measures, including timely OS update, application and database update, virus update, virus and trojan scan, security scan, and a good security policy, putting data on your computer is often not as safe as you think. From recent DDoS attacks, we know that a very large portion of computers have been infected with trojans unknowingly. Therefore, using a good cloud solution is often safer than storing your data on an unprotected PC.</p>\r\n");
      out.write("\r\n<a name=\"kept\"></a>\r\n<h1>How long will my data be kept?</h1>\r\n<p>Ragic will hold on to your data as long as you have a Ragic account. If you accidentally deleted a sheet or a database from your account, there's a good chance we can still save it. Just <a href=\"/support/rs\">submit a ticket</a> and we'll see what we can do.</p>\r\n\r\n<a name=\"install\"></a>\r\n<h1>Can I install Ragic on my own computer or servers?</h1>\r\n<p>Yes, if you still would like to keep the data on your own servers. We provide easily installable versions of Ragic.</p>\r\n\r\n<a name=\"many\"></a>\r\n<h1>Are there any limits to how many or how big my applications are?</h1>\r\n<p>For details on account types and their limits, please see our <a href=\"register\">pricing page</a>. We limit application sizes by storage space, not number of records, and you can always <a href=\"/support/rs\">contact support</a> for more storage spaces.</p>\r\n\r\n<a name=\"publish\"></a>\r\n<h1>Is there any place where developers can publish their own apps?</h1>\r\n<p>Our <a href=\"enterpriseApps\">Applications</a> page contains sample applications that we built to give you an idea of how Ragic works. We will begin to publish great applications built by our Ragic developer community soon, so if you have a great application on your account, <a href=\"mailto:support@ragic.com\">e-mail us</a>!</p>\r\n");
      out.write("\r\n<a name=\"mean\"></a>\r\n<h1>What does Ragic mean?</h1>\r\n<p>Ragic = Rapid + Magic</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n</div>");
